cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the use of steganography, which involves hiding information within images, and the potential for using Facebook as a platform for this technique. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Other likely categories include cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as these categories may also be relevant to the topic of image steganography on Facebook.
